1
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:52,969
DEAR X

2
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,764
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND EVENTS
IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,474
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED
WITH GUARDIANS PRESENT

4
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,434
Wedding, you say?

5
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:04,981
I'll wipe away
all the stains from your past.

6
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:08,318
And you'll start over by my side.

7
00:01:09,402 --> 00:01:10,403
What do you say?

8
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,615
No need to overthink it.

9
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:15,700
All you have to do

10
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,870
is just nod.

11
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,789
Then everything will get easier.

12
00:01:22,207 --> 00:01:25,543
A safe, solid fence...

13
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:28,797
That's what I need.

14
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:32,467
Are you saying you can give me that?

15
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:40,433
I'll give you anything.

16
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:43,603
Can you prove what you just said?

17
00:01:47,357 --> 00:01:50,318
You need proof for my words?

18
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,154
Say it anyway.

19
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:56,908
That if I take your hand

20
00:01:58,076 --> 00:02:01,204
I'll be able to do everything I want.

21
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:11,965
Shit.

22
00:02:13,216 --> 00:02:14,384
You okay?

23
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,147
Move!

24
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,608
We have to get out of here.

25
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,372
Are you okay?

26
00:02:44,455 --> 00:02:45,999
We need to move.

27
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:06,978
I promise you, Ah-jin.

28
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:10,023
Come to me.

29
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:37,008
EPISODE 10: THE MONSTER IN THE MIRROR

30
00:03:42,055 --> 00:03:43,514
Is Boss still not picking up?

31
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:47,435
I need to go.

32
00:03:47,518 --> 00:03:48,519
To her place?

33
00:03:49,145 --> 00:03:50,146
Yes.

34
00:03:51,522 --> 00:03:53,650
This is definitely connected to her.

35
00:03:58,571 --> 00:03:59,948
Yes, Mr. Hong.

36
00:04:06,621 --> 00:04:07,622
I understand.

37
00:04:17,882 --> 00:04:21,594
I should get going.
Grandpa's in critical condition.

38
00:04:23,012 --> 00:04:24,931
Can you try to find Ah-jin?

39
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,099
Please.

40
00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:27,725
Okay, I'll take care of it.

41
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:21,988
REST IN PEACE

42
00:05:22,071 --> 00:05:26,326
THE LATE YOON SEUNG-MO
GRANDSON: YOON JUN-SEO

43
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,192
Gosh, I can finally digest a little.

44
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:25,987
When it's time to go

45
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:31,826
dying at the right time is
also a blessing.

46
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:33,119
Excuse me!

47
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:34,996
Here!

48
00:07:35,705 --> 00:07:37,999
One bowl of stew here!

49
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,460
Gosh.

50
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,379
Jeez, you're so slow.

51
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,849
I got through to the boss.

52
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,643
It seems like nothing's wrong.

53
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:58,978
She says she'll call later.

54
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:00,897
Okay.

55
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:06,819
I'm off.

56
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:19,290
Seriously, a new bag drops
even before a whole season passes.

57
00:08:19,373 --> 00:08:22,126
It's like they don't want me
to keep the ones I have.

58
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:28,132
And all I see at the department store
are the exact same bags.

59
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:31,385
Right.

60
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,305
They seem to be in good condition.

61
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:37,642
And most of them are
close to new, so...

62
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:39,435
So?

63
00:08:43,397 --> 00:08:44,398
How much are they?

64
00:08:46,692 --> 00:08:47,735
Ms. Sim Sung-hee?

65
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:50,571
- Yes?
- Hello.

66
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:56,244
Judging by that reaction,
you're definitely guilty.

67
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,162
You know why we're here, right?

68
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,293
How would I know?

69
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:08,881
Okay.

70
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,216
Sure.

71
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:12,260
That was Ah-jin, right?

72
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:15,304
She admitted she gave them
to me, didn't she?

73
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:17,515
Let her go.

74
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:19,684
Yes, sir.

75
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:25,815
Have a good day, guys.

76
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:36,450
Do I have to pick up calls
from the police because of you?

77
00:09:40,746 --> 00:09:42,290
I was just...

78
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,586
I mean, you don't have a job now

79
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,838
so I figured
I'd sell things to help you out.

80
00:09:49,589 --> 00:09:50,840
By selling my stuff?

81
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:56,178
You're a known celebrity.

82
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:58,472
It'd be embarrassing for you
to show up with these.

83
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:00,224
So, I was just helping you out.

84
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:03,894
Hey, I wasn't going to keep it all.

85
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,064
I was at least going to split it
50-50 with you.

86
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:10,484
You're unbelievable, Sung-hee.

87
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:14,780
If you don't like 50-50, then 60-40.

88
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:18,909
If you don't like 60-40, then 70-30!

89
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:21,037
I'm fine with only 30 percent.

90
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:33,007
Mr. Hong!

91
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:35,134
I've been waiting ages for you.

92
00:10:35,217 --> 00:10:36,427
Have a drink with me.

93
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,763
No, ma'am. I have work to do.

94
00:10:38,846 --> 00:10:40,097
What work?

95
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:42,433
It's not like the dead man will care.

96
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,768
Sit.

97
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,228
Sit down.

98
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:47,647
Do you know how long I waited?

99
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:49,440
All right.

100
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:52,777
Have a drink. Loosen up a bit.

101
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,320
Cheers.

102
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,452
You're quite the professional.

103
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:10,795
So, how was the inheritance settled?

104
00:11:10,878 --> 00:11:14,924
I'm the only daughter-in-law
of this family, after all.

105
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:20,221
There was no mention of your share.

106
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:25,476
Out of all that money,
not a single piece for me?

107
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:27,311
Not even ten won?

108
00:11:28,729 --> 00:11:33,150
Most of it was left
to your son, Jun-seo--

109
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,736
He's the grandson.
Of course, he gets something.

110
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:37,446
I'm talking about me.

111
00:11:39,615 --> 00:11:40,616
How...

112
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:44,161
How could a man who doted
on his grandson, whom I raised

113
00:11:44,245 --> 00:11:45,621
do this to me?

114
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,289
How could he?

115
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,084
Ma'am, legally and morally

116
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:51,794
there's no reason
you'd receive an inheritance.

117
00:11:51,877 --> 00:11:53,921
Jun-seo gets it, but why not me?

118
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,798
I'm not asking for the same amount.

119
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:58,384
Even a quarter or a tenth!

120
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,845
He should have considered me
at least that much!

121
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:12,648
Strictly speaking

122
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:15,443
you and the late Chairman Yoon
are completely unrelated.

123
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,944
Unrelated?

124
00:12:17,027 --> 00:12:18,362
Did you just call me unrelated?

125
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:20,448
Thanks for bringing that up.

126
00:12:20,531 --> 00:12:22,908
Then is he his bloodline?

127
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:24,785
He's also unrelated!

128
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:27,997
Who do you think continued
this family line with no heirs?

129
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,876
Even if I gave birth to and raised
someone else's child

130
00:12:31,959 --> 00:12:35,004
I made him a grandson worthy enough

131
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:37,256
to be in this family!

132
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,384
Ungrateful old man.

133
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:42,928
I should have killed him.

134
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:46,932
What did you just say?

135
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:51,854
Jun-seo!

136
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,732
I raised you!

137
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:59,987
Now, pay me back,
adjusted for inflation!

138
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:03,240
A hundredfold!

139
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:22,009
You made me part of this family's
bloodline for inheritance?

140
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:25,721
And you lied to me my whole life?

141
00:13:28,849 --> 00:13:31,936
Yes, I did.

142
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:33,270
So what?

143
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,481
Why?

144
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:41,070
Why do you always live like this?

145
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:43,155
That's how everybody lives.

146
00:13:43,239 --> 00:13:45,533
Those people in that funeral hall?

147
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:49,578
They're all circling for scraps
from the old man's estate.

148
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:54,416
They only pretend to be noble
on the outside.

149
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,752
- Mom.
- I'm not the only one who lied.

150
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,337
She also knew.

151
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:00,464
Baek Ah-jin, that skank, knew.

152
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:04,927
That little nine-year-old
started threatening me since then.

153
00:14:05,886 --> 00:14:06,887
She drove

154
00:14:07,555 --> 00:14:10,558
a wedge between us

155
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:12,601
and toyed with you.

156
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:15,312
Is that why you hit her?

157
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,984
You lied about me
being this family's son

158
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,527
and brought her
into the house for that.

159
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,737
It was all you.

160
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:29,994
I...

161
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:33,581
always knew...

162
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:38,627
you were a bad person.

163
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:42,423
Yet I still pitied you.

164
00:14:44,174 --> 00:14:46,594
I thought, "She must be struggling.

165
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:48,888
That's why she's like that."

166
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:59,982
I tried to understand you.
I tried so hard.

167
00:15:00,065 --> 00:15:03,819
And with Ah-jin,
I thought I should pay the price.

168
00:15:05,654 --> 00:15:07,156
But why did you do that to me?

169
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,172
It was for you.

170
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:30,137
So you could live with a good father.

171
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:34,391
I didn't want you
inheriting my poverty.

172
00:15:39,146 --> 00:15:42,066
So, from the very beginning

173
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:46,654
I was never
the true grandson of Grandpa

174
00:15:46,737 --> 00:15:49,114
and the wounds she's carried
all her life were because of me.

175
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:04,672
Sure. Keep thinking that.

176
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,008
Haunted by the past forever.

177
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:12,012
Pathetic.

178
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:30,656
Hey.

179
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,491
Get out.

180
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:34,535
Baek Ah-jin.

181
00:16:35,619 --> 00:16:36,912
You know this, right?

182
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:40,958
After I dropped out of high school,
my family collapsed.

183
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:44,169
That's when everything went
wrong for me.

184
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:45,921
So?

185
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:48,048
What's that got to do with me?

186
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,927
Why did you do that to me back then?

187
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:55,806
I want an apology, though it's late.

188
00:16:56,807 --> 00:16:57,808
Sung-hee.

189
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:01,437
Apologies are for people
who did something wrong.

190
00:17:03,772 --> 00:17:06,191
Are you not even a little sorry?

191
00:17:09,236 --> 00:17:10,571
Why would I be?

192
00:17:10,654 --> 00:17:14,074
You lost because you got greedy
trying to beat me.

193
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:17,161
You were clueless, stupid

194
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:19,788
and had no awareness
of your place or the situation.

195
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,250
And you kept poking at me.

196
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:30,674
You just got unlucky.

197
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:34,970
Happy?

198
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:46,440
Bitch.

199
00:18:12,674 --> 00:18:14,426
Why are you here this late?

200
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,553
And where are you going this late?

201
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,472
I heard about your grandfather.

202
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,224
I was going to call later--

203
00:18:20,891 --> 00:18:23,352
You won't even take my calls now.
When exactly is later?

204
00:18:28,607 --> 00:18:31,026
Your mom got a kidney from you

205
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:33,278
your grandfather died

206
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:35,322
and now you come
to take it out on me?

207
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:39,034
Do I have to pick up your calls
on command?

208
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:40,702
Sorry

209
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:43,330
but I don't have the luxury
of waiting by the phone for you.

210
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:45,040
I told you to wait.

211
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:48,418
If you waited, I would come to you.
That was the one thing I asked you.

212
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:50,003
And you couldn't even do that?

213
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,800
You knew I was an illegitimate child

214
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:00,639
and that I had
a different biological father.

215
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:03,684
Is that true?

216
00:19:06,770 --> 00:19:07,771
It's not, right?

217
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,524
So, you finally found out.

218
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:15,946
Now you know
why I went through all that.

219
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:19,324
How does it feel now?

220
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:21,827
Relieved?

221
00:19:30,878 --> 00:19:32,254
Why did you lie to me?

222
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:33,338
Jun-seo.

223
00:19:35,424 --> 00:19:37,259
I never lied to you.

224
00:19:38,051 --> 00:19:40,053
I just didn't tell you.

225
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:43,307
And shouldn't you be grateful to me?

226
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:46,435
Because you were kept in the dark

227
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:49,313
you got help from your grandfather

228
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:51,648
lived in a nice home,
and wrote in peace.

229
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,443
If I had told you then

230
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:57,863
how different
would your life have been?

231
00:19:58,405 --> 00:20:01,909
You would have run away,
hidden, or suffered

232
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,076
like an idiot.

233
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:06,246
So...

234
00:20:09,541 --> 00:20:12,085
you're saying you did that for me?

235
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:13,420
Yes.

236
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:15,881
Can you say I'm wrong?

237
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:20,135
Everything you enjoyed
because you were Yoon Jun-seo.

238
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:21,845
Can you deny all of that?

239
00:20:24,723 --> 00:20:26,225
This is why I didn't tell you.

240
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,561
Because you wouldn't be able
to handle it.

241
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:30,979
I would have endured.

242
00:20:33,857 --> 00:20:36,443
If you hadn't lied
or hid it from me...

243
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:42,157
If you had told me
that you suffered because of me...

244
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:47,913
I would have endured
anything for you.

245
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:52,084
Somehow.

246
00:22:35,062 --> 00:22:36,355
- Hello, ma'am.
- Hello, ma'am.

247
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:10,031
Actress Baek Ah-jin
and CEO Moon Do-hyuk

248
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,868
have officially tied the knot,
holding a wedding ceremony

249
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:14,786
at a cathedral in Sicily.

250
00:24:14,870 --> 00:24:18,123
As the marriage between a top actress
and a chaebol businessman

251
00:24:18,206 --> 00:24:20,167
their union has been dubbed
the wedding of the century

252
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:23,003
drawing widespread attention.

253
00:24:23,086 --> 00:24:25,547
Speculation continues about
where the newlyweds will establish...

254
00:24:27,215 --> 00:24:28,550
She's out of the picture.

255
00:24:30,343 --> 00:24:31,511
- What?
- Kid.

256
00:24:31,595 --> 00:24:33,180
My instincts are razor sharp.

257
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:35,599
Baek Ah-jin. She's the broom, right?

258
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,061
Hey.

259
00:24:42,647 --> 00:24:44,691
- Do you know this man?
- Of course.

260
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,527
Who in Korea doesn't know
Moon Do-hyuk?

261
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,654
He's rich, handsome, and competent.

262
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:50,739
He's perfect.

263
00:24:52,824 --> 00:24:55,327
Anyway, it's over now that
she married into a chaebol family.

264
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,956
She achieved every woman's dream.
Just wish her well now.

265
00:25:00,457 --> 00:25:02,167
Once she's with a guy like that...

266
00:25:05,086 --> 00:25:06,588
even stalkers would give up.

267
00:25:08,381 --> 00:25:09,549
You should let her go, too.

268
00:25:12,219 --> 00:25:15,722
And the office fire turned out to be
a simple electrical short.

269
00:25:16,097 --> 00:25:18,934
Why spin stories
about warnings and threats?

270
00:25:32,531 --> 00:25:33,532
Sure.

271
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:35,951
I guess that's all it was.

272
00:25:45,126 --> 00:25:46,628
Can you say I'm wrong?

273
00:25:48,463 --> 00:25:51,591
Everything you enjoyed
because you were Yoon Jun-seo.

274
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,177
Can you deny all of that?

275
00:26:09,734 --> 00:26:11,403
LENA

276
00:26:19,077 --> 00:26:20,287
Will you be gone long?

277
00:26:21,621 --> 00:26:22,747
Yes.

278
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,416
A very long time.

279
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:27,669
I won't come back at all if I can.

280
00:26:28,461 --> 00:26:30,547
Text me if you get bored.

281
00:26:32,465 --> 00:26:33,466
I won't.

282
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:37,846
I might want to come back home.

283
00:26:39,139 --> 00:26:40,599
Can I give you a piece of advice?

284
00:26:41,725 --> 00:26:44,144
Get away from Baek Ah-jin, too.

285
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:47,147
I'm not telling you to come to me.

286
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:51,860
But I hope that you will live
your own life now.

287
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:55,322
As human Yoon Jun-seo.

288
00:26:58,825 --> 00:26:59,826
Yes.

289
00:27:00,619 --> 00:27:01,620
I will.

290
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:06,791
And I'm not going to write anymore.

291
00:27:08,251 --> 00:27:10,503
- I doubt it.
- I mean it.

292
00:27:12,213 --> 00:27:14,924
I'm putting down writing,
and I'm letting go of Ah-jin.

293
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:17,469
I want to give myself some time.

294
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:18,845
Good choice.

295
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:21,264
You might finally start acting
like a human being.

296
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:23,141
Too bad I won't be around to see it.

297
00:27:23,535 --> 00:27:25,535
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

298
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,936
Take care.

299
00:27:40,867 --> 00:27:41,868
I'm leaving.

300
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:58,802
AMEN TO NOTHING

301
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:56,317
I want to look around a bit.
Can you open the door?

302
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:59,863
I'm afraid only Mr. Moon is allowed
into the third-floor study, ma'am.

303
00:29:04,659 --> 00:29:05,660
Is that right?

304
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:10,331
I just want to look.

305
00:29:11,124 --> 00:29:12,250
I can't even do that?

306
00:29:13,918 --> 00:29:15,837
Am I not also
the master of this house?

307
00:29:22,218 --> 00:29:26,347
Even the previous madam
wasn't allowed.

308
00:29:26,431 --> 00:29:28,349
It's entirely
Mr. Moon's private space.

309
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:30,769
That makes me feel weird.

310
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:39,319
If she wasn't allowed,
does that mean I'm also not allowed?

311
00:29:42,197 --> 00:29:43,907
I'm a little hurt, Ms. Gong.

312
00:29:44,824 --> 00:29:48,036
I'm not her, you know.

313
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:49,245
If you insist

314
00:29:50,997 --> 00:29:53,291
- perhaps you could speak with--
- Forget it.

315
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:15,021
The movie shoot starts
next week, right?

316
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:17,440
How do you feel?

317
00:30:18,191 --> 00:30:20,610
It's the project you wanted so badly.

318
00:30:20,693 --> 00:30:21,694
Not bad.

319
00:30:22,862 --> 00:30:24,447
Thanks to my capable husband

320
00:30:24,531 --> 00:30:26,366
I met a skilled director.

321
00:30:26,449 --> 00:30:27,826
I guess I'm a little excited.

322
00:30:44,592 --> 00:30:47,512
What does it feel like
to get everything you want?

323
00:30:49,973 --> 00:30:51,182
Mostly boring.

324
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:53,852
Especially when it's easy.

325
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:55,979
Was I easy to get?

326
00:30:58,731 --> 00:31:00,191
You know the answer.

327
00:31:01,359 --> 00:31:05,154
You were someone
I invested a lot of effort into.

328
00:31:05,238 --> 00:31:07,198
So, it felt the best
when I finally had you.

329
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:11,369
That's why I brought you
a major film so quickly.

330
00:31:14,914 --> 00:31:16,291
Do you have any other questions?

331
00:31:21,671 --> 00:31:23,715
Can I use your study

332
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:25,174
on the third floor?

333
00:31:29,012 --> 00:31:30,430
The study?

334
00:31:32,056 --> 00:31:33,224
Why?

335
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:38,313
It's hard to concentrate
on my script.

336
00:31:39,147 --> 00:31:41,232
I want a quiet space to practice

337
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:42,942
but the house is always crowded.

338
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:53,328
The study won't magically make you
practice better, though.

339
00:31:53,995 --> 00:31:56,497
I'll practice with you instead.

340
00:31:56,998 --> 00:31:57,999
You will?

341
00:31:58,541 --> 00:31:59,542
Yes.

342
00:32:07,550 --> 00:32:09,636
Just read this section.

343
00:32:11,512 --> 00:32:13,556
- Let's see.
- But

344
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,224
are you sure you can handle it?

345
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:18,853
What kind of character
am I supposed to play?

346
00:32:19,270 --> 00:32:21,189
It would help to know
so I can match the tone.

347
00:32:23,191 --> 00:32:25,818
He's the real culprit
behind the murder

348
00:32:25,902 --> 00:32:27,695
of the protagonist's family.

349
00:32:29,405 --> 00:32:31,032
I take revenge on him later.

350
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:34,077
A murderer, then.

351
00:32:35,578 --> 00:32:37,664
Have you ever killed anyone?

352
00:32:39,582 --> 00:32:41,584
- Pardon?
- Or did you have

353
00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:43,252
anyone you wanted to kill?

354
00:32:48,091 --> 00:32:49,133
Do-hyuk?

355
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:51,844
Did I ever tell you

356
00:32:53,054 --> 00:32:54,597
why I divorced my ex-wife?

357
00:32:56,057 --> 00:32:59,727
She kept saying she wanted to kill me

358
00:33:00,770 --> 00:33:01,854
so I divorced her.

359
00:33:05,149 --> 00:33:08,820
I gave her everything she wanted
and treated her like royalty.

360
00:33:08,903 --> 00:33:10,405
Maybe that's why.

361
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:13,408
Whenever something went
slightly wrong or didn't satisfy her

362
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:15,034
she couldn't handle it.

363
00:33:15,326 --> 00:33:16,536
She blamed everything on me

364
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:18,913
saying that I made her that way.

365
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:25,044
Eventually,
she had a complete breakdown.

366
00:33:25,128 --> 00:33:27,171
Now she's being treated
in a psychiatric hospital.

367
00:33:29,298 --> 00:33:33,136
Maybe I treated her too well,
above her place.

368
00:33:34,470 --> 00:33:36,097
It broke my heart.

369
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:42,311
Did I shock you?

370
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:46,774
I went off track, didn't I?

371
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:48,109
Not really.

372
00:34:01,414 --> 00:34:03,291
Ready, action!

373
00:34:14,635 --> 00:34:16,637
Sister, I know
who killed your family.

374
00:34:19,474 --> 00:34:20,850
It's someone you know.

375
00:34:39,285 --> 00:34:41,287
- I'll go ahead and order first.
- Sure.

376
00:34:53,883 --> 00:34:55,843
Have you ever killed anyone?

377
00:34:56,219 --> 00:34:58,221
- Pardon?
- Or did you have

378
00:34:58,304 --> 00:34:59,931
anyone you wanted to kill?

379
00:35:03,643 --> 00:35:05,103
What a psycho.

380
00:35:08,314 --> 00:35:12,151
They say Baek Ah-jin's husband
got her this role.

381
00:35:12,235 --> 00:35:14,862
Figures. I thought it was weird
how public opinion flipped overnight

382
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:17,031
after her image collapsed like that.

383
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:18,533
Someone must have pulled strings.

384
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:22,120
Man, I wish I had
a rich husband, too.

385
00:35:22,203 --> 00:35:23,871
I'd live however I want.

386
00:35:23,955 --> 00:35:24,956
Seriously.

387
00:35:25,039 --> 00:35:27,250
Life is so unpredictable.

388
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:30,586
Who knew she'd break up
with Heo In-gang like that

389
00:35:30,962 --> 00:35:34,048
and immediately marry
into a chaebol family?

390
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:37,218
She obviously married him for money.

391
00:35:37,301 --> 00:35:39,220
It won't last.

392
00:35:39,303 --> 00:35:41,389
Bet they'll have
divorce rumors next year.

393
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,142
Hey, that was a little harsh.

394
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:48,479
Enjoy your coffee.

395
00:36:00,074 --> 00:36:04,495
RIP
THE LATE YOON SEUNG-MO

396
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:23,973
Thank you.

397
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:28,060
Thank you for taking me in...

398
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:31,397
and raising me.

399
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:37,153
And I'm sorry.

400
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:42,200
I don't think I can come back.

401
00:37:23,032 --> 00:37:24,450
FOR MENSTRUAL CRAMPS

402
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:33,602
Who brought this here?

403
00:38:54,832 --> 00:38:55,833
You're home.

404
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:58,794
You're early today.

405
00:39:00,004 --> 00:39:01,005
Yes.

406
00:39:02,965 --> 00:39:04,508
How was today's shoot?

407
00:39:04,592 --> 00:39:05,676
Did you do well?

408
00:39:06,886 --> 00:39:08,012
Of course.

409
00:39:10,723 --> 00:39:12,433
You look a bit tired.

410
00:39:12,516 --> 00:39:14,185
Are you feeling unwell?

411
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:17,438
Do-hyuk.

412
00:39:18,647 --> 00:39:20,316
There's something I want to ask.

413
00:39:25,279 --> 00:39:27,698
Never mind. Maybe I'm just tired.

414
00:39:31,619 --> 00:39:33,204
You don't seem to have a fever.

415
00:39:34,038 --> 00:39:35,539
Are you sure you're okay?

416
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:38,376
It's just fatigue.

417
00:39:39,085 --> 00:39:40,336
I'm fine.

418
00:39:40,419 --> 00:39:41,420
All right.

419
00:39:42,296 --> 00:39:43,964
Then I'll go shower.

420
00:39:44,048 --> 00:39:45,216
Get some rest in the meantime.

421
00:40:07,321 --> 00:40:08,989
Since when was it like this?

422
00:40:09,365 --> 00:40:10,449
I apologize, ma'am.

423
00:40:10,533 --> 00:40:12,660
I noticed it was broken this morning

424
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:14,995
but I forgot
because things got hectic.

425
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:16,497
I'll fix it right away.

426
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:44,733
You're just waiting
for time to pass, aren't you?

427
00:40:44,817 --> 00:40:45,818
But too bad for you.

428
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:51,198
The moment you want so badly
will never come.

429
00:42:07,483 --> 00:42:08,901
What happened to you?

430
00:42:08,984 --> 00:42:10,694
You never call me out first.

431
00:42:18,994 --> 00:42:20,120
You okay?

432
00:42:22,998 --> 00:42:24,917
You look better than I expected.

433
00:42:30,589 --> 00:42:34,552
I thought you'd be moping around
like some lost puppy.

434
00:42:34,635 --> 00:42:35,636
This guy.

435
00:42:38,097 --> 00:42:39,098
What is it?

436
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:41,225
Why did you call me?

437
00:42:41,976 --> 00:42:43,143
Something's going on, right?

438
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:46,564
I called you to drink.
We're at a bar. Why else?

439
00:42:48,983 --> 00:42:50,317
You're too old
for teenage turmoil now.

440
00:42:54,113 --> 00:42:55,197
What about you?

441
00:42:55,614 --> 00:42:57,575
I've always wondered.

442
00:42:57,658 --> 00:42:59,577
How do you sacrifice your whole life

443
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:02,454
just for the sake of another person?

444
00:43:08,294 --> 00:43:10,504
My life isn't worth

445
00:43:11,755 --> 00:43:13,048
betting on.

446
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:16,343
I'm the delinquent son
who killed his own dad.

447
00:43:17,177 --> 00:43:18,762
No family wants me

448
00:43:20,055 --> 00:43:21,807
nor do I have a clue what I live for.

449
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:23,934
Who's going to complain

450
00:43:25,019 --> 00:43:27,896
if I bet a life like that
on someone else?

451
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:43,037
You should start

452
00:43:44,121 --> 00:43:45,456
living your own life.

453
00:43:47,916 --> 00:43:51,045
So you don't end up like me,
not knowing where to go.

454
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:52,713
Idiot.

455
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:56,133
You're so fucking drunk right now.

456
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:00,304
Excuse me.

457
00:44:00,596 --> 00:44:02,473
I'll handle my life.

458
00:44:02,556 --> 00:44:05,017
You deal with yours.

459
00:44:05,100 --> 00:44:07,019
You're the one acting pitiful.

460
00:44:07,102 --> 00:44:08,354
Who's the lost puppy here?

461
00:44:08,771 --> 00:44:09,772
Unbelievable.

462
00:44:11,565 --> 00:44:12,566
Jun-seo.

463
00:44:13,567 --> 00:44:15,027
If you don't know where to go

464
00:44:16,111 --> 00:44:17,279
do you want me to show you?

465
00:44:25,412 --> 00:44:27,873
Let's go for Round Two.
You're paying.

466
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:29,541
Deal?

467
00:44:42,388 --> 00:44:43,931
Lady!

468
00:44:44,014 --> 00:44:46,558
Lady, are you done yet?

469
00:44:46,642 --> 00:44:48,769
Gosh, you're so slow.
Hurry up already.

470
00:44:48,852 --> 00:44:49,853
Yes, ma'am.

471
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:02,783
I'm here.

472
00:45:03,867 --> 00:45:04,868
You came.

473
00:45:06,203 --> 00:45:07,204
Good.

474
00:45:19,049 --> 00:45:21,343
- Ms. Baek, please say a word!
- A comment, please!

475
00:45:21,427 --> 00:45:23,262
- Will there be another movie?
- About your return!

476
00:45:23,345 --> 00:45:24,346
Ms. Baek Ah-jin!

477
00:45:27,224 --> 00:45:29,518
- Just one comment!
- Ms. Baek Ah-jin!

478
00:45:43,282 --> 00:45:44,283
Excuse me.

479
00:45:58,130 --> 00:45:59,131
Long time no see.

480
00:46:04,636 --> 00:46:07,139
How did you recognize me?

481
00:46:07,514 --> 00:46:10,476
How could I not?
You were staring at me from there.

482
00:46:14,313 --> 00:46:16,148
But what brings you here?

483
00:46:16,732 --> 00:46:18,275
Nothing, well...

484
00:46:18,358 --> 00:46:20,819
You just stopped contacting me

485
00:46:20,903 --> 00:46:23,405
and I haven't seen you in a while.

486
00:46:23,822 --> 00:46:26,909
So, I just wanted to check
if you were doing okay.

487
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:33,999
You are okay, right?

488
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:36,919
You look pale.

489
00:46:37,002 --> 00:46:38,712
There's no life in your face
as if you're sick.

490
00:46:39,838 --> 00:46:40,839
I'm not sure

491
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:43,634
if I'm doing okay.

492
00:46:46,553 --> 00:46:48,680
It's just that I've been having
nightmares every night.

493
00:46:49,348 --> 00:46:50,349
I'm just tired.

494
00:46:58,398 --> 00:47:00,275
What?

495
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:01,944
Did you fall for me or something?

496
00:47:02,027 --> 00:47:03,904
Stop staring.

497
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:07,157
Hey, Jae-oh.

498
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:10,244
Can you look
into Moon Do-hyuk for me?

499
00:47:11,161 --> 00:47:12,162
Moon Do-hyuk?

500
00:47:13,121 --> 00:47:14,331
Your husband?

501
00:47:18,961 --> 00:47:19,962
I knew it.

502
00:47:20,212 --> 00:47:22,214
That bastard was up to something,
wasn't he?

503
00:47:22,297 --> 00:47:23,590
It's not that.

504
00:47:23,674 --> 00:47:25,342
I just have a weird feeling.

505
00:47:25,676 --> 00:47:28,178
Find out about his ex-wife in detail.

506
00:47:28,971 --> 00:47:30,264
And where she is now.

507
00:47:30,597 --> 00:47:32,182
Even better
if I can talk to her in person.

508
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:33,308
Hold on.

509
00:47:33,392 --> 00:47:35,227
He had an ex-wife?

510
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:36,937
So, he's been married before?

511
00:47:39,231 --> 00:47:40,232
Jeez.

512
00:47:41,024 --> 00:47:43,193
I knew I hated that guy from day one.

513
00:47:43,819 --> 00:47:45,571
Why are you getting mad?

514
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:48,198
Why did you marry

515
00:47:48,448 --> 00:47:51,076
someone like him?
You're way out of his league.

516
00:47:51,577 --> 00:47:53,370
Cut the nonsense.

517
00:47:53,453 --> 00:47:55,706
- Can you do it or not?
- Don't even bother asking.

518
00:47:55,789 --> 00:47:59,501
Just wait. I'll dig up everything
and won't leave a single detail out.

519
00:48:16,476 --> 00:48:20,480
Ma'am, have some warm tea before bed.

520
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:23,692
I don't want any.

521
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:30,741
After that day,
Mr. Moon insisted that you drink it.

522
00:48:35,996 --> 00:48:39,791
If you refuse, he'll get on my case.

523
00:49:33,470 --> 00:49:34,513
Where's Ah-jin?

524
00:51:09,649 --> 00:51:12,527
Such lovely weather, ma'am.

525
00:51:13,236 --> 00:51:15,530
I wish every day were like this.

526
00:51:16,823 --> 00:51:17,824
Right?

527
00:51:27,584 --> 00:51:32,297
"I pray that every path I take
be cursed with blood."

528
00:52:07,082 --> 00:52:08,708
AMEN TO NOTHING

529
00:53:48,683 --> 00:53:51,686
It fucking pissed me off even more
when I thought about it.

530
00:53:52,270 --> 00:53:55,649
I crawled into your house
just to watch you fall

531
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:57,859
and this is how you treat me?

532
00:53:59,945 --> 00:54:02,489
My whole life is ruined
because of you.

533
00:54:03,198 --> 00:54:04,366
And you...

534
00:54:04,741 --> 00:54:05,742
It's not fair

535
00:54:06,952 --> 00:54:11,039
you get to rise even higher
and live in this mansion.

536
00:54:13,750 --> 00:54:14,960
Who said you could?

537
00:54:16,336 --> 00:54:18,296
You will never get away from me!

538
00:54:27,013 --> 00:54:29,307
Why you?

539
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:32,477
Why does a devil like you
get to do well?

540
00:54:35,313 --> 00:54:36,314
Sung-hee.

541
00:54:36,898 --> 00:54:40,527
You failed because you were stupid.
Don't blame other people.

542
00:54:41,361 --> 00:54:44,030
Fine. If I can't be like you
because I'm stupid

543
00:54:44,114 --> 00:54:46,074
you can become like me.

544
00:54:46,157 --> 00:54:48,618
Right? That's easier, isn't it?

545
00:54:48,702 --> 00:54:50,328
Dragging you down to the bottom.

546
00:54:53,623 --> 00:54:56,751
You're also finished
if that pretty face gets ruined.

547
00:55:00,338 --> 00:55:01,339
But Ah-jin

548
00:55:02,007 --> 00:55:03,091
you know what?

549
00:55:04,884 --> 00:55:08,096
Do you think your marriage is

550
00:55:08,179 --> 00:55:09,306
a blessing or a curse?

551
00:55:11,850 --> 00:55:13,643
Your husband...

552
00:55:45,383 --> 00:55:46,509
Sung-hee.

553
00:56:32,514 --> 00:56:36,601
DEAR X

554
00:58:57,075 --> 00:58:59,077
Subtitles by Ho-young Yun
